Package: gstudio
License: GPL (>= 2)
Title: Tools Related to the Spatial Analysis of Genetic Marker Data
Type: Package
Authors@R: person(given = c("Rodney", "J."),
    family = "Dyer",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "rjdyer@vcu.edu")
Description: Provides classes and functions for the spatial analysis of
    genetic marker data, including population structure, genetic diversity,
    distance, and relatedness statistics. This package introduces the S3 'locus'
    class (allowing loci to be in the same data frame as your non-genetic data)
    for storing, manipulating, and querying multilocus genotype data. It
    implements standard estimators for genetic diversity, genetic distance,
    and population differentiation. Crucially, this version incorporates the
    network construction and analysis capabilities of the previously separate 
    'popgraph' package, representing population genetic structure as graph-theoretic 
    networks as described in Dyer and Nason (2004) <doi:10.1111/j.1365-294X.2004.02177.x> 
    and Dyer (2015) <doi:10.1146/annurev-ecolsys-112414-054150>. It also provides 
    newly developed, state-of-the-art methods for evaluating network asymmetry, 
    conditional introgression pressures, and directional gene flow using local Gaussian 
    kernels and perplexity-tuned Markov flow partitioning. Integration with spatial 
    and geographic data is provided via compatibility with 'sf', 'sp', 'ggplot2', 
    and interactive leaflet maps.
